<article id="comment-353460" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/aeMCtIk7PQjvF4H4kg5jPr5SHuMwhSErASX7mV5t9eU0l3eHn2dm0VNXA_QHaOMU39WHdPDeWxhh8CA7C4at4nFqSSNVxpKC5Uu_NwSCR8F0nb-_IBt-8x2vw512-h288-nc.jpg" width="50" height="28" alt="Yuan-Niisan" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>Yuan-Niisan</b> <br/><br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-3-chapter-1-1/#comment-353460"><time datetime="2016-05-19T07:00:20+00:00"> May 19, 2016 at 7:00 am</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>Everything Xuan did have the pros and cons. He was a walking computer. Atleast he lets them have two options and would not force them to submit to him. It would be disaster if they decided to antagonize him. And to their current mental condition, they would really either listen to him or jump into the death pit. Even me would be greatly relieved if i have that one person with me. And, just imagine if Xuan wasn&#8217;t in their team? They would not have any idea you could exchange for gunpowders and important factors to survive. He held no deep feelings to anyone, he was a researcher afterall. His mind was set to make the risk factors as low as possible.</p>
</div> 
